params.__sweepTargets: The addresses that can be swept by the fee collector.
params._factoryConfig: The variables that configure the factory.

params._initializeExtraData: The extra data for the `initialize` call.

params.index: The index of the instance to get.

returns._0: The instance at the specified index.

params.endIndex: The ending index of the instances to get.
params.startIndex: The starting index of the instances to get.

returns.range: The resulting custom portion of the _instances array.

returns._0: The number of instances deployed by this factory.

params._defaultPausers_: The new list of default pausers.

params._fees: The new defaults for the fee parameters.

deployAndInitialize((address,address,byt.notice: This deploys and initializes a new ERC4626Hyperdrive instance.

feeCollector().notice: The fee collector used when new instances are deployed.

fees().notice: The fee parameters used when new instances are deployed.

getInstanceAtIndex(uint256).notice: Gets the instance at the specified index.

getInstancesInRange(uint256,uint256).notice: Returns the _instances array according to specified indices.

getNumberOfInstances().notice: Gets the number of instances deployed by this factory.

governance().notice: The governance address that updates the factory's configuration.

hyperdriveDeployer().notice: The contract used to deploy new instances of Hyperdrive.

hyperdriveGovernance().notice: The governance address used when new instances are deployed.

isOfficial(address).notice: A mapping from deployed Hyperdrive instances to the version         of the deployer that deployed them.

linkerCodeHash().notice: The linker code hash used when new instances are deployed.

linkerFactory().notice: The linker factory used when new instances are deployed.

target0Deployer().notice: The contract used to deploy new instances of Hyperdrive.

target1Deployer().notice: The contract used to deploy new instances of Hyperdrive.

updateDefaultPausers(address[]).notice: Allows governance to change the default pausers.

updateFeeCollector(address).notice: Allows governance to change the fee collector address.

updateFees((uint256,uint256,uint256)).notice: Allows governance to update the default fee schedule that will         be used in new deployments.

updateGovernance(address).notice: Allows governance to transfer the governance role.

updateHyperdriveGovernance(address).notice: Allows governance to change the hyperdrive governance address

updateImplementation(address).notice: Allows governance to update the deployer contract.

updateLinkerCodeHash(bytes32).notice: Allows governance to change the linker code hash. This allows         governance to update the implementation of the ERC20Forwarder.

updateLinkerFactory(address).notice: Allows governance to change the linker factory.

updateSweepTargets(address[]).notice: Allows governance to change the sweep targets used in deployed         instances.

versionCounter().notice: The number of times the factory's deployer has been updated.
